.TH man 3 "27 June 2023" "0.01" " _printf man page"
.SH NAME
.B _printf
- A simple recrestion of the printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
To use this function the header file #include main.h" is needed.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf() function produces output according to a format which is descried below. 
This function write its output to the stdout(the standard output stream).
.SH USAGE
To use _printf you have to use the following key characters preceeded by % symbol.
.RS 3
%c: To print a  character(s)
.RS 0
%s: To print string of characters
.RS 0
%d: To print integers of max and min size of an int type
.RS 0
%i: To print integrs of max and min size of an int type
.RS 0
%b: To print a number in binary form
.SH RETURN VALUES
The _printf() function returns an integer which shows the number of symbols 
printed not counting for the string
.SH SEE ALSO
.I printf(3)
.SH BUGS
no known bugs.
